The Party-list System Act imposes that party-lists are barred from participating in elections if they advocate violence or unlawful means to seek its goal. Since the CPP-NPA is involved in multiple acts of violence since its establishment, this means all party-lists under them can not participate in the 2022 elections. If the GWP is a legal front of the CPP-NPA, then they should not be in the final listing of elections. However, that is not the case as they are included in the list which implies that they have not violated any laws and regulations. Thus, the statement is false.

Since the CPP-NPA is involved in multiple acts of violence since its establishment, this means all party-lists under them can not participate in the 2022 elections. If the GWP is indeed part of the CPP-NPA, then they should not be in the final listing of elections. However, that is not the case as they are included in the list which implies that they have not violated any laws and regulations. Thus, the statement is false.
